// =============================================================================
// Infandoku-3D v3 — 9×9×9 Sudoku Solver
//
// IMPROVEMENTS vs v2 (from README roadmap):
//
//  [A] Gen-Counter MRV Cache
//      domain_size[x][y][z] caches popcount. cur_gen bumped each DFS node.
//      Cache entry valid iff domain_gen[x][y][z] == cur_gen.
//      MRV scan reads cache instead of recomputing popcount every node.
//      Expected gain: ×1.5 on MRV overhead.
//
//  [B] Watched Literals (WL)
//      Each (line, digit) pair watches 2 cells. When one watcher is eliminated,
//      we try to find a new watcher in that line. If no watcher found, the
//      other watcher is the only cell that can hold the digit → force it (HS).
//      This replaces the full O(N^3) hidden-singles scan with O(delta) checks.
//      Expected gain: ×2–4 on hard instances.
//
//  [C] Naked Pairs 3D
//      In any group of 9, if two cells share the same 2-candidate bitmask,
//      those two digits can be eliminated from all other cells in that group.
//      Applied to all 324 groups after HS in the propagation loop.
//      Expected gain: reduces backtracking on hard instances.
//
//  [D] LCV (Least Constraining Value)
//      When branching on MRV cell, try digit values in order of increasing
//      impact (fewest eliminations first). Approximated by counting how many
//      peer cells still carry that digit — cheapest to compute.
//      Expected gain: ×1.2–2 on hard instances.
//
//  [E] Conflict-Driven Backjumping (CBJ)
//      Each cell tracks which DFS decision level last touched it (conflict set).
//      On contradiction, we jump back to the highest-level decision in the
//      conflict set instead of just one level up.
//      Expected gain: large on highly constrained instances.
//
// COMPILE
//   g++ -O3 -march=native -std=c++17 -o infandoku_3d infandoku_3d.cpp
// =============================================================================

